Academic All-Big Ten (2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

Big Ten Distinguished Scholar (2023, 2024)

College Sports Communicators Academic All-America First Team (2024)

College Sports Communicators Academic All-America Third Team (2023)

Big Ten Medal of Honor (2024)

2023-24 (Graduate Student)

Placed fifth in the 100 free at the NCAA Championships with a time of 47.18

Was the Big Ten Champion in the 100 free for the second straight year, finishing in a time of 47.48

Was on the Big Ten Champion 400 medley relay and on the third place 400 free relay team

At the conference championships, finished second in the 50 free (21.79) and sixth in the 200 free (1:44.77)

Qualified for the U.S. Olympic Team Trials in the 50 back, 100 back, 50 free and 100 free

Placed 15th in the 50 free semifinals with a time of 25.23

2022-23 (Senior)

At the NCAA Championships, was on the fourth place 200 free relay, fifth place 400 free relay and sixth place 400 medley relay teams, as well as the 13th place 800 free relay team

Also ar the NCAA Championships, placed ninth in the 100 free (47.39) and 12th in the 200 free (1:43.78)

Was the Big Ten Champion in the 100 free with a time of 47.02, which is a school record

Also earned Big Ten titles in the 400 free relay and 400 medley relay

Was a medalist in both the 200 free and 50 free at the Big Ten Championships

At the Indy Spring Cup over the summer, set Olympic Trials qualifying times in the 50 free (25.32), 100 free (54.78), and 100 back (1:00.46)

2021-22 (Junior)

Was on the third place 200 medley relay, fourth place 200 free relay and 400 medley relay, and eighth place 400 free relay teams at the NCAA Championships

Placed 11th in the 50 free at the NCAA Championships

Earned Big Ten titles in the 800 free relay, 400 medley relay, and 200 free relay

Placed second in both the 50 free and 100 free at the Big Ten Championships

2020-21 (Sophomore)

Won the 400 Free Relay twice in Ohio Stateâ€™s three meet regular season

Picked up wins in the 200 and 100 Free to go undefeated in the triangular against Rutgers and Purdue

Won a Big Ten title with the 200 Free Relay team and earned points in five other events to help the Buckeyes to the 2021 Big Ten Championship

Earned All-America honors in the 200, 400 and 800 Free Relays

2019-20 (Freshman)

Had a great first season, earning All-America honors in three events and winning a Big Ten title as part of the 200 Free Relay Team

Was part of a total of eight relay victories on the season and also posted a win in the 50 Free vs. Denison in November

Swam a personal best 1:52.07 in the 200 Free at the Shamrock Invitational

Was tremendous at her first Big Ten Championship, earning points in five different events and helping the team to a team title

Qualified for the B final of the 50 Free and swam a personal best 22.27 to finish second and 10th overall

Swam a then personal best 53.48 in the prelims of the 100 Back only to better that time to 53.40 and wound up finishing third in the B final

Was part of the 200 Free Relay that set a pool record en route to claiming the Big Ten title in 1:27.57

Finished seventh overall in the 100 Free after notching a personal best 48.44 in the prelims

Capped the meet by helping the 400 Free Relay team to a runner-up finish in a school-record time of 3:13.06

Prior to Ohio State

Four year letterwinner in swimming and golf at Bellefontaine High School

Ran track for one season

Three-time CBC winners for golf and Sportsmanship Award winner (2017)

Top point scorer for swimming all four years

Competed in Freestyle and Backstroke

Four-time CBC swimmer of the year

Finished second in freestyle and backstroke at states for her highest finishes in four years

Named captain her senior season

Personal

Daughter of Gregg and Pam Fulmer

Has three siblings, Emily, Sarah and John

Sister, Emily swims at Ohio Wesleyan

Would like to attend medical school and pursue a career as a specialized doctor

Involved in the Honors and Scholars program at OSU
